qas.question: What people established a settlement in what is now the St. Mary's area of Southampton?
What name did the Anglo-Saxons give their settlement first?
What name did Hamwic have in the interim as it was evolving into Hampton?
What county in England was named after Hampton?
What river separated Hamwic from the home of previous settlers?

context: The <a0_0>Anglo-Saxons<a0_0/> formed a new, larger, settlement across the <a4_0>Itchen<a4_0/> centred on what is now the St Mary's area of the city. The settlement was known as <a1_0>Hamwic<a1_0/>, which evolved into <a2_0>Hamtun<a2_0/> and then Hampton. Archaeological excavations of this site have uncovered one of the best collections of Saxon artefacts in Europe. It is from this town that the county of <a3_0>Hampshire<a3_0/> gets its name.
